modules.description: Represents a time value with nanosecond precision using `tv_sec` and `tv_nsec` fields. Provides direct access to system time values typically used in low-level time operations and conversions. Useful for interfacing with system calls that require precise time measurements or timestamps.

This module provides operations for working with high-precision time values using the `Timespec` structure, which stores time in seconds and nanoseconds. It supports direct access to system time values, enabling precise time measurements and conversions. Concrete use cases include timestamping events, measuring execution duration, and interfacing with system calls that require exact time specifications.

This module provides functions for working with high-resolution time values, specifically for measuring and manipulating time intervals in seconds and nanoseconds. It supports operations like getting the current time, adding or subtracting time intervals, and comparing timestamps with precise resolution. Concrete use cases include performance benchmarking, scheduling tasks with fine-grained timing, and handling time-based events in concurrent systems.

This module handles high-resolution time measurements and manipulations, offering operations to retrieve the current time, perform arithmetic on time intervals, and compare timestamps with nanosecond precision. It works primarily with time values represented as seconds and nanoseconds, enabling accurate timing for performance-critical applications. Use cases include benchmarking code execution, implementing precise delays, and coordinating time-sensitive operations in concurrent programs.
